This paper focuses on studying multilingualism in Wikipedia using a computational approach, which involves analyzing a large dataset of content written by multilingual editors. The paper discusses language proficiency, engagement, and interests of these editors, which are all relevant to the fields of computational linguistics (cs.CL), social informatics (cs.SI), cybernetics (cs.CY), scientific data management (cs.SD), and digital libraries (cs.DL). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
